🛒 E-commerce Backend (Monolithic Architecture)

🚀 Overview

This project is a production-ready Spring Boot monolithic backend for an e-commerce system.
It demonstrates backend engineering concepts from basic CRUD to scalable API design.

---

🧠 Key Features

👤 User Management

- Create, fetch, and delete users
- DTO-based request/response handling
- Validation support

📦 Product Management

- Create products linked to users (seller concept)
- Pagination & sorting support
- Search/filter products by name

🛍️ Order Management

- Place orders with user & product
- Server-side total price calculation (secure design)
- Transactional consistency

---

🏗️ Architecture

Feature-based (modular monolith):

com.aviraj.ecommerce
│
├── user/
├── product/
├── order/
├── common/
│   ├── exception/
│   ├── response/

Why this structure?

- Easy to scale
- Microservice-ready
- Clean separation of concerns

---

⚙️ Tech Stack

- Java 17
- Spring Boot
- Spring Data JPA
- H2 Database
- Maven

---

🔥 Advanced Concepts Implemented

- DTO Pattern (Request/Response separation)
- Global Exception Handling
- Validation ("@Valid", "@NotNull", etc.)
- Pagination & Sorting ("Pageable")
- Filtering using JPA methods
- Logging using SLF4J
- Transaction Management ("@Transactional")
- Standard API Response Wrapper

---

📡 API Examples

Create Product

POST "/products"

{
  "name": "Laptop",
  "price": 75000,
  "userId": 1
}

---

Get Products (Pagination)

GET "/products?page=0&size=5"

---

Search Products

GET "/products/search?keyword=laptop"

---

Place Order

POST "/orders"

{
  "userId": 1,
  "productId": 1,
  "quantity": 2
}

---

🧠 Design Decisions

- Used double for price (temporary) → will be replaced with BigDecimal in future
- User acts as both buyer and seller
- Backend calculates price → avoids client-side manipulation

---

🚀 Future Enhancements

- Microservices architecture
- Inter-service communication (REST/Feign)
- API Gateway
- Service discovery
- Distributed transactions
- Authentication & Authorization

